x4freetext: N-PULSE WIDTH OF 200 NS(BEFORE MODERATION), TIME
CHANNEL WIDTH OF 125 NS, NOMINAL RESOLUTION OF 16NS/M.
4 ENRICHED SAMPLES (MORE THAN 80 PERC. IN WEIGHT)
IN BA-134,135,136,137 AND 1 OF NATURAL BARIUM.
TIME OF FLIGHT, FLIGHT PATH = 14.5 M.
THAT ALL RESONANCES WERE DUE TO S-WAVE INTERACTIONS.
RESONANCE AT 24.4 EV SEEMS TO BE S-WAVE, NO ASYMMETRY
APPEARS DUE TO INTERACTION BETWEEN S-WAVE RESONANCE
.GAMMA WIDTHS ARE ASSUMED AS 100 MILLI-EV EXCEPT THOSE
DATA ESSENTIALLY FROM TABLE 2,PAG.397 OF NP/A,177,393
